1 Killed , 22 Wounded in Blast in Eastern Turkey
ANKARA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- One person was killed and 22 others wounded early Thursday morning when a bomb exploded in eastern Turkey , the Anatolia News Agency reported .
The agency said that the bomb attack was targeted against a military vehicle carrying soldiers in the city of Van .
It said the killed was a student nearby the military vehicle , and several soldiers were among the 22 injured .
No one has claimed responsibility for the attack .
But in the past , Kurdish rebels were often suspected as perpetrators .
The injured were rushed to hospitals in the city for treatment , said the agency .
An investigation into the incident is underway .
